5|$|In 1904, E.V. Ramasamy went on {{a pilgrimage}} to Kasi to visit the revered Siva temple of Kashi Vishwanath. Though {{regarded}} as one of the holiest sites of <b>Hinduism,</b> he witnessed immoral activities such as begging, and floating dead bodies. His frustrations extended to functional <b>Hinduism</b> in general when he experienced what he called Brahmanic exploitation.|$|E
