50|$|The five {{faces of}} Pashupatinath {{represent}} various incarnations of Shiva; Sadyojata (also known as Barun), Vamdeva (also known as Uma Maheswara), Tatpurusha, Aghor & Ishana. They face West, North, East, South and Zenith respectively, and represent <b>Hinduism's</b> five primary elements namely earth, water, air, light and ether.|$|R
50|$|Kabir (कबीर, IAST: Kabīr) was a 15th-century Indian mystic {{poet and}} saint, whose {{writings}} influenced <b>Hinduism's</b> Bhakti movement and his verses {{are found in}} Sikhism's scripture Adi Granth. His early life was in a Muslim family, but he was strongly influenced by his teacher, the Hindu bhakti leader Ramananda.|$|R
